-- Belgium Almost Closed Trade Gap in March, National Bank Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   C l a p h a m
-- 2013-05-16T13:09:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/belgium-closed-trade-gap-in-march-national-bank-says.html
Belgium almost erased its trade
deficit in March, the  National Bank of Belgium  said.  The deficit narrowed to 40.5 million euros from a revised
395 million euros in February, the central bank said on its
website. March exports fell 2.3 percent to 22 billion euros,
while imports dropped 3.5 percent to 22.1 billion euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Clapham in Brussels at 
